Source: Ashburton Guardian
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: "All lands in any district or subdivision, which by their altitude, configuration, or other physical causes are excluded from deriving any possible benefit from a water-race, shall be exempted from all rates to be levied in respect of such water race;  and also all lands which are supplied with water from springs, streams, or private water races thereon shall also be so exempted from rates unless the owners thereof respectively consent to the same being levied."
